---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';

const mcpConfig = `{
  "mcpServers": {
    "mailctl":   { "command": "mailctl",   "args": ["mcp"] },
    "calctl":    { "command": "calctl",    "args": ["mcp"] },
    "taskctl":   { "command": "taskctl",   "args": ["mcp"] },
    "notectl":   { "command": "notectl",   "args": ["mcp"] },
    "budgetctl": { "command": "budgetctl", "args": ["mcp"] },
    "diaryctl":  { "command": "diaryctl",  "args": ["mcp"] },
    "timectl":   { "command": "timectl",   "args": ["mcp"] },
    "postctl":   { "command": "postctl",   "args": ["mcp"] }
  }
}`;

const navSections = [
  {
    title: 'Getting Started',
    links: [
      { href: '#installation', label: 'Installation' },
      { href: '#quick-setup', label: 'Quick Setup' },
      { href: '#claude-config', label: 'Claude Desktop config' },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Tools',
    links: [
      { href: '#mailctl', label: 'mailctl' },
      { href: '#calctl', label: 'calctl' },
      { href: '#taskctl', label: 'taskctl' },
      { href: '#notectl', label: 'notectl' },
      { href: '#budgetctl', label: 'budgetctl' },
      { href: '#diaryctl', label: 'diaryctl' },
      { href: '#timectl', label: 'timectl' },
      { href: '#postctl', label: 'postctl' },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Reference',
    links: [
      { href: '#mcp-reference', label: 'MCP Reference' },
      { href: '#ai-workflows', label: 'AI Workflows' },
    ],
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Documentation — missionctl"
  description="Complete documentation for all 8 missionctl tools. Installation, CLI reference, TUI keybindings, and MCP tool reference for mailctl, calctl, taskctl, notectl, budgetctl, diaryctl, timectl, and postctl."
>
  <!-- Mobile sidebar nav -->
  <details class="docs-mobile-nav">
    <summary>Documentation <span style="color:#4a5568; font-size:0.7rem;">&#9660;</span></summary>
    <nav>
      {navSections.map(s => s.links.map(l => (
        <a href={l.href}>{l.label}</a>
      )))}
    </nav>
  </details>

  <div class="docs-layout">
    <!-- Sidebar -->
    <aside class="docs-sidebar">
      <div class="docs-sidebar-inner">
        <nav class="docs-nav">
          {navSections.map(section => (
            <div class="docs-nav-section">
              <p class="docs-nav-section-title">{section.title}</p>
              <div class={section.title === 'Tools' ? 'docs-nav-sub' : ''}>
                {section.links.map(link => (
                  <a href={link.href} data-href={link.href}>{link.label}</a>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </nav>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <!-- Main content -->
    <div class="docs-main">
      <h1>missionctl Documentation</h1>
      <p style="color:#718096; margin-bottom:2rem;">
        52 MCP tools across 8 terminal apps. Local-first, no cloud, no subscriptions.
      </p>

      <!-- ── GETTING STARTED ───────────────── -->
      <h2 id="getting-started">Getting Started</h2>

      <h3 id="installation">Installation</h3>
      <p>Clone and build each tool. Every repo has a <code>setup.sh</code> that compiles the binary and installs it to <code>~/.local/bin/</code>.</p>
      <pre><code>{`for repo in mailctl calctl taskctl notectl budgetctl; do
  git clone https://github.com/aeon022/$repo
  cd $repo && ./setup.sh && cd ..
done`}</code></pre>
      <p>Make sure <code>~/.local/bin</code> is on your <code>$PATH</code>:</p>
      <pre><code>{`export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
# add to ~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc`}</code></pre>

      <h3 id="quick-setup">Initial Sync</h3>
      <p>After installing, run the initial sync for each tool to populate the local SQLite cache:</p>
      <pre><code>{`mailctl sync      # Apple Mail → local cache
calctl sync       # Apple Calendar → local cache
taskctl sync      # Apple Reminders → local cache
notectl sync      # Obsidian vault → local index`}</code></pre>
      <p><strong>budgetctl</strong> is import-driven — there's no background sync:</p>
      <pre><code>{`budgetctl import bank.csv --account checking`}</code></pre>

      <h3 id="claude-config">Claude Desktop Config</h3>
      <p>
        Add all 6 tools to Claude Desktop in one config block. Edit
        <code>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code>:
      </p>
      <pre><code set:text={mcpConfig}></code></pre>
      <p>Restart Claude Desktop. All 52 MCP tools appear automatically in every conversation.</p>

      <!-- ── MAILCTL ───────────────────────── -->
      <h2 id="mailctl">mailctl</h2>
      <p>
        Apple Mail bridge with TUI inbox, full-text search, compose, and 6 MCP tools.
        Syncs Apple Mail into a local SQLite database — all reads happen locally.
      </p>

      <h3>Install</h3>
      <pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/aeon022/mailctl
cd mailctl && ./setup.sh`}</code></pre>

      <h3>Sync</h3>
      <pre><code>{`mailctl sync          # sync inbox
mailctl sync --all    # sync all folders`}</code></pre>

      <h3>CLI commands</h3>
      <pre><code>{`mailctl inbox                    # open TUI inbox
mailctl inbox --json             # JSON output
mailctl search "from:alice"      # search emails
mailctl send --to bob@x.com      # compose & send
mailctl draft --subject "Hello"  # save to Drafts
mailctl thread --subject "Re:"   # view thread
mailctl accounts                 # list accounts
mailctl mcp                      # start MCP server`}</code></pre>

      <h3>TUI keybindings</h3>
      <div class="docs-kbd-grid">
        <kbd>j / k</kbd>     <span>Navigate up/down</span>
        <kbd>Enter</kbd>     <span>Open selected email</span>
        <kbd>n</kbd>         <span>Compose new email</span>
        <kbd>s</kbd>         <span>Sync inbox</span>
        <kbd>/</kbd>         <span>Search</span>
        <kbd>d</kbd>         <span>Delete email</span>
        <kbd>U</kbd>         <span>Unsubscribe</span>
        <kbd>q</kbd>         <span>Quit</span>
      </div>

      <h3>MCP tools</h3>
      <div>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">inbox</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">search_email</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">email_thread</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">send_email</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">draft_email</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">sync_inbox</span>
      </div>

      <!-- ── CALCTL ────────────────────────── -->
      <h2 id="calctl">calctl</h2>
      <p>
        Apple Calendar bridge. Browse events, create events, find free slots.
        Requires macOS — talks to Apple Calendar via AppleScript and EventKit.
      </p>

      <h3>Install</h3>
      <pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/aeon022/calctl
cd calctl && ./setup.sh`}</code></pre>

      <h3>Sync</h3>
      <pre><code>{`calctl sync           # sync next 30 days
calctl sync --days 90 # sync 90 days`}</code></pre>

      <h3>CLI commands</h3>
      <pre><code>{`calctl list                         # list upcoming events
calctl list --from 2026-07-01       # events from date
calctl add "Team sync" --time 14:00 # create event
calctl free --from today --to +7d   # find free slots
calctl sync                         # sync calendar
calctl mcp                          # start MCP server`}</code></pre>

      <h3>TUI keybindings</h3>
      <div class="docs-kbd-grid">
        <kbd>j / k</kbd>   <span>Navigate events</span>
        <kbd>Enter</kbd>   <span>Open event detail</span>
        <kbd>n</kbd>       <span>Create new event</span>
        <kbd>s</kbd>       <span>Sync calendar</span>
        <kbd>/</kbd>       <span>Search events</span>
        <kbd>q</kbd>       <span>Quit</span>
      </div>

      <h3>MCP tools</h3>
      <div>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">list_events</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">today</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">this_week</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">find_free_slots</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">create_event</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">delete_event</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">sync</span>
      </div>

      <!-- ── TASKCTL ───────────────────────── -->
      <h2 id="taskctl">taskctl</h2>
      <p>
        Apple Reminders bridge with TUI task manager, built-in Pomodoro timer,
        background sync daemon, and batch operations.
      </p>

      <h3>Install</h3>
      <pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/aeon022/taskctl
cd taskctl && ./setup.sh`}</code></pre>

      <h3>Sync</h3>
      <pre><code>{`taskctl sync           # sync Apple Reminders
taskctl daemon         # start background sync daemon`}</code></pre>

      <h3>CLI commands</h3>
      <pre><code>{`taskctl list                         # list all tasks
taskctl today                        # today's tasks
taskctl week                         # this week's tasks
taskctl add "Review PR" --due today  # create task
taskctl done <id>                    # mark complete
taskctl lists                        # list reminder lists
taskctl daemon                       # background daemon
taskctl mcp                          # start MCP server`}</code></pre>

      <h3>TUI keybindings</h3>
      <div class="docs-kbd-grid">
        <kbd>j / k</kbd>   <span>Navigate tasks</span>
        <kbd>Space</kbd>   <span>Toggle task complete</span>
        <kbd>n</kbd>       <span>New task</span>
        <kbd>i</kbd>       <span>Inline edit title</span>
        <kbd>e</kbd>       <span>Full edit</span>
        <kbd>d</kbd>       <span>Delete task</span>
        <kbd>s</kbd>       <span>Sync</span>
        <kbd>t</kbd>       <span>Focus mode / Pomodoro</span>
        <kbd>p</kbd>       <span>Pomodoro timer</span>
        <kbd>A</kbd>       <span>Batch select</span>
        <kbd>q</kbd>       <span>Quit</span>
      </div>

      <h3>MCP tools</h3>
      <div>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">today_tasks</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">week_tasks</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">list_tasks</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">sync</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">create_task</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">complete_task</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">delete_task</span>
      </div>

      <!-- ── NOTECTL ───────────────────────── -->
      <h2 id="notectl">notectl</h2>
      <p>
        Obsidian vault bridge. Sync notes to local SQLite, read/write notes, search,
        and manage daily notes. Works on macOS and Linux.
      </p>

      <h3>Install</h3>
      <pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/aeon022/notectl
cd notectl && ./setup.sh`}</code></pre>

      <h3>Config</h3>
      <p>Edit <code>~/.config/notectl/notectl.yaml</code>:</p>
      <pre><code>{`vault_path: ~/Documents/Obsidian/MyVault
source: obsidian`}</code></pre>

      <h3>Sync</h3>
      <pre><code>{`notectl sync      # index vault into SQLite cache`}</code></pre>

      <h3>CLI commands</h3>
      <pre><code>{`notectl list                    # list notes
notectl read "Note title"       # read a note
notectl write "New note"        # create/update note
notectl search "keyword"        # full-text search
notectl daily                   # open today's daily note
notectl mcp                     # start MCP server`}</code></pre>

      <h3>TUI keybindings</h3>
      <div class="docs-kbd-grid">
        <kbd>j / k</kbd>   <span>Navigate notes</span>
        <kbd>Enter</kbd>   <span>Open note</span>
        <kbd>n</kbd>       <span>New note</span>
        <kbd>e</kbd>       <span>Edit note</span>
        <kbd>d</kbd>       <span>Delete note</span>
        <kbd>o</kbd>       <span>Open in $EDITOR</span>
        <kbd>s</kbd>       <span>Sync vault</span>
        <kbd>/</kbd>       <span>Search</span>
        <kbd>Tab</kbd>     <span>Browse folders</span>
        <kbd>q</kbd>       <span>Quit</span>
      </div>

      <h3>MCP tools</h3>
      <div>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">list_notes</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">read_note</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">write_note</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">search_notes</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">sync_notes</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">get_daily_note</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">append_daily_note</span>
      </div>

      <!-- ── BUDGETCTL ─────────────────────── -->
      <h2 id="budgetctl">budgetctl</h2>
      <p>
        Personal finance tool. Import bank CSVs, categorize transactions with rules,
        set budget goals, and detect recurring payments. Works on macOS and Linux.
      </p>

      <h3>Install</h3>
      <pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/aeon022/budgetctl
cd budgetctl && ./setup.sh`}</code></pre>

      <h3>Import</h3>
      <pre><code>{`budgetctl import bank.csv --account checking
budgetctl import n26.csv --format n26
# Supported: N26, ING, DKB, Generic CSV`}</code></pre>

      <h3>CLI commands</h3>
      <pre><code>{`budgetctl list                      # list transactions
budgetctl list --month 2026-07      # filter by month
budgetctl summary                   # income/expense summary
budgetctl summary --month 2026-07   # monthly summary
budgetctl tag "Netflix" --category subscriptions
budgetctl apply-rules               # re-apply all rules
budgetctl goal set --category food --limit 400
budgetctl goal list                 # show goals + progress
budgetctl goal delete --category food
budgetctl recurring                 # detect recurring payments
budgetctl export --format csv       # export data
budgetctl mcp                       # start MCP server`}</code></pre>

      <h3>TUI keybindings</h3>
      <div class="docs-kbd-grid">
        <kbd>j / k</kbd>         <span>Navigate transactions</span>
        <kbd>s</kbd>             <span>Monthly summary</span>
        <kbd>S</kbd>             <span>Sync / reimport</span>
        <kbd>/</kbd>             <span>Search transactions</span>
        <kbd>Tab / Shift+Tab</kbd> <span>Navigate months</span>
        <kbd>q</kbd>             <span>Quit</span>
      </div>

      <h3>MCP tools</h3>
      <div>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">list_transactions</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">budget_summary</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">import_transactions</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">tag_transactions</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">apply_category_rules</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">list_budget_goals</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">set_budget_goal</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">delete_budget_goal</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">detect_recurring_payments</span>
      </div>

      <!-- ── POSTCTL ───────────────────────── -->
      <h2 id="postctl">postctl</h2>
      <p>
        Social media scheduling for Threads, Bluesky, Mastodon, Twitter, LinkedIn, Telegram, and Discord. Manage posts,
        campaigns, and drafts from your terminal.
        Available at <a href="https://postctl.sh" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:#00d97e;">postctl.sh</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Install</h3>
      <pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/aeon022/postctl
cd postctl && ./setup.sh`}</code></pre>

      <h3>CLI commands</h3>
      <pre><code>{`postctl list                         # list posts
postctl post "Hello world"           # create post
postctl post --schedule "2026-07-05 09:00" "Hello"
postctl publish <id>                 # publish post immediately
postctl cancel <id>                  # cancel scheduled post
postctl delete <id>                  # delete post locally & remotely
postctl daemon                       # start scheduler daemon
postctl campaign list                # list campaigns
postctl import posts.csv             # import posts
postctl mcp                          # start MCP server`}</code></pre>

      <h3>TUI keybindings</h3>
      <div class="docs-kbd-grid">
        <kbd>j / k</kbd>   <span>Navigate posts/history</span>
        <kbd>Space</kbd>   <span>Select / deselect post for bulk actions</span>
        <kbd>p</kbd>       <span>Publish selected post(s) immediately</span>
        <kbd>s</kbd>       <span>Schedule post to next queue slot</span>
        <kbd>e</kbd>       <span>Edit post content</span>
        <kbd>n</kbd>       <span>Create new post</span>
        <kbd>d</kbd>       <span>Delete post locally and remotely</span>
        <kbd>r</kbd>       <span>Repurpose post content via AI</span>
        <kbd>f</kbd>       <span>Filter by campaign</span>
        <kbd>x</kbd>       <span>Export history</span>
        <kbd>R / F1</kbd>  <span>Open README documentation</span>
        <kbd>q</kbd>       <span>Quit</span>
      </div>

      <h3>Safety &amp; Spam Protection</h3>
      <p>
        To avoid rate limits and account bans, <code>postctl</code> includes built-in safeguards:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Queue spacing:</strong> Scheduled queue slots are spaced out automatically.</li>
        <li><strong>Overdue protection:</strong> If multiple scheduled posts become overdue (e.g., system was offline), only the oldest is posted immediately. The subsequent posts are automatically rescheduled in 20-minute intervals.</li>
        <li><strong>Safe remote deletion:</strong> Deleting a post locally automatically issues API delete calls to the remote platforms to keep feeds in sync.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>MCP tools</h3>
      <div>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">list_posts</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">get_post</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">create_post</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">publish_post</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">schedule_post</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">list_campaigns</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">get_campaign</span>
      </div>

      <!-- ── DIARYCTL ──────────────────────── -->
      <h2 id="diaryctl">diaryctl</h2>
      <p>
        Developer diary from your terminal. Reads git history, completed tasks (taskctl),
        calendar events (calctl), and time logs (timectl) to generate AI narrative diary entries.
      </p>

      <h3>Install</h3>
      <pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/aeon022/diaryctl
cd diaryctl && ./setup.sh`}</code></pre>

      <h3>Setup</h3>
      <pre><code>{`diaryctl init ~/code/myproject --name "My Project"
diaryctl repos   # list registered repos`}</code></pre>

      <h3>CLI commands</h3>
      <pre><code>{`diaryctl today               # generate today's entry
diaryctl today --open        # open in $EDITOR
diaryctl list                # list all entries
diaryctl show 2026-07-04     # show a specific entry
diaryctl stats --days 30     # coding stats for last 30 days
diaryctl tui                 # open TUI (heatmap + list)
diaryctl mcp                 # start MCP server`}</code></pre>

      <h3>TUI keybindings</h3>
      <pre><code>{`j/k     navigate entries
enter   open entry
n       generate today's entry
e       edit in $EDITOR
r       repos view
v       stats view
q       quit`}</code></pre>

      <h3>MCP tools</h3>
      <div>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">get_today_stats</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">get_diary_entry</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">write_diary_entry</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">get_coding_stats</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">list_diary_entries</span>
      </div>

      <!-- ── TIMECTL ──────────────────────── -->
      <h2 id="timectl">timectl</h2>
      <p>
        Time tracking from your terminal. Start and stop timers, view a weekly bar chart,
        and integrate time logs into diaryctl diary entries.
      </p>

      <h3>Install</h3>
      <pre><code>{`git clone https://github.com/aeon022/timectl
cd timectl && ./setup.sh`}</code></pre>

      <h3>CLI commands</h3>
      <pre><code>{`timectl start "Fix auth bug" --project myapp
timectl stop
timectl status               # check running timer
timectl today                # time log for today
timectl week                 # weekly bar chart
timectl log --days 7         # last 7 days log
timectl tui                  # open TUI
timectl mcp                  # start MCP server`}</code></pre>

      <h3>TUI keybindings</h3>
      <pre><code>{`n       start new timer
s       stop running timer
j/k     navigate log
w       week view
v       stats view
q       quit`}</code></pre>

      <h3>MCP tools</h3>
      <div>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">start_timer</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">stop_timer</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">get_time_log</span>
        <span class="docs-tool-tag">get_time_stats</span>
      </div>

